edu.berkeley.cs.jqf.examples.jgrapht

Annotation Type GraphModel


  • @Target(value={PARAMETER,FIELD,ANNOTATION_TYPE,TYPE_USE})
 @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @GeneratorConfiguration
public @interface GraphModel
    Configures a graph generator to generate graphs using a GNM or GNP model.
    Author:
    Rohan Padhye

    • Required Element Summary

      Required Elements 
      Modifier and Type Required Element and Description
      int nodes
      The number of nodes to generate.

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      int edges
      The number of edges to generate.
      boolean loops
      Whether self-loops are allowed.
      boolean multiGraph
      Whether multiple edges are allowed.
      double p
      The probability of generating an edge between a pair of nodes.
      boolean weighted
      Whether to generate random weights for the graph's edges.

    • Element Detail

      • nodes

        public abstract int nodes
        The number of nodes to generate. Must be provided.
        Returns:
        the number of nodes to generate

      • edges

        public abstract int edges
        The number of edges to generate. If provided, a GNM model is used for generation, and the p value is ignored.
        Returns:
        a value greater than or equal to zero.
        See Also:
        GNM model
        Default:
        0

      • p

        public abstract double p
        The probability of generating an edge between a pair of nodes. This value is ignored if edges is provided. If this value is considered, a GNP model is used for generation.
        Returns:
        a value between 0.0 and 1.0.
        See Also:
        GNP model
        Default:
        1.0

      • weighted

        public abstract boolean weighted
        Whether to generate random weights for the graph's edges. If false, all edges will have a default edge-weight of 1.0.
        Returns:
        whether random edge weights should be generated
        Default:
        false

      • loops

        public abstract boolean loops
        Whether self-loops are allowed.
        Returns:
        whether self-loops are allowed
        Default:
        false

      • multiGraph

        public abstract boolean multiGraph
        Whether multiple edges are allowed.
        Returns:
        whether multiple edges are allowed
        Default:
        false
